his Sunday dress. About 10 o'clock in the morning, 
they would be on their way to church, And it looked

25:52.700 --> 26:06.148
as if the divets of white, pink, blue, red, yellow, 
and the variegated colors had outrivaled

25:52.700 --> 26:06.148
themselves in putting out the brightest colors of 
which their dresses were made from. Every pattern

26:07.371 --> 26:12.902
wrote on the plate was filled with those who were 
going to church. and the woods rang with their joy

26:13.523 --> 26:18.729
and happiness and their calls to each other. 
Morning there, Sister Maisie. How's y'all? Oh,

26:22.653 --> 26:24.315
I'se tired but well, thank you. How's y'all? 
That's sure am a pretty dress what you got on.

26:29.601 --> 26:31.883
Where'd you get it? You're going out to shine all 
them niggas in Old Rose Church today. Yes, ma'am,

26:37.129 --> 26:40.312
you sure is going out to shine us all. Now you shut 
your mouth, Jean. You know you're just poking fun

26:43.409 --> 26:45.652
at me? How's your ma? Where's Fanny? Oh, she 
coming. She got herself all dressed up. She say

26:52.721 --> 26:57.347
she'd whine to get happy today and beat the very 
stepping out of that gal of Susie. But I tell her, if

26:57.887 --> 27:02.774
that's the spirit she's whining to church in, she 
gotta stay at home. But she promised me that she'd

27:03.434 --> 27:08.401
behave herself and be one of the first mooners on 
the beach. And I tell her she can come on to church.

27:11.422 --> 27:18.732
This was only preliminary of what would take place 
when they all met under the big oak trees on the

27:11.422 --> 27:18.732
